  "notes": "Lingala (lingála), Bantu lingua franca of the Congo river basin. Literary Lingala has a seven-vowel system /a e ɛ i o ɔ u/ written with the IPA letters ⟨ɛ ɔ⟩; spoken Lingala reduces this to five. Prenasalised sequences are written ⟨mb mp nd ng nk ns nt nz⟩ and ⟨gb⟩ is the labial-velar /ɡ͡b/. Lingala is tonal — the acute marks high tone, the circumflex falling and the caron rising — but tone is NOT emitted here: the accented vowels map to the same phoneme as their plain counterparts so that accented text still transcribes.",
